    <item>
      <title>Exporting Winlogbeat Logs to SOF-ELK</title>
      <link>https://opforge.dev/docs/winlogbeat-export/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 10 May 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://opforge.dev/docs/winlogbeat-export/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;-purpose&#34;&gt;🔍 Purpose&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Enable structured Windows event logs to flow from OPFORGE&amp;rsquo;s Windows Member VM to SOF-ELK using Winlogbeat, a JSON exporter, and PowerShell automation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;-prerequisites&#34;&gt;✅ Prerequisites&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Windows 10/11 host joined to domain (e.g., &lt;code&gt;OPF-MBR01&lt;/code&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Winlogbeat installed and configured&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SSH access to SOF-ELK (e.g., &lt;code&gt;elk_user@192.168.77.40&lt;/code&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Valid PuTTY key pair (&lt;code&gt;.ppk&lt;/code&gt;) for SCP transfers (if using PSCP)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Target folder on SOF-ELK writable by &lt;code&gt;elk_user&lt;/code&gt; (e.g., &lt;code&gt;/logstash/kape/&lt;/code&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;-checkdocheck-workflow&#34;&gt;🔧 Check–Do–Check Workflow&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;-check&#34;&gt;🔍 Check&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confirm Winlogbeat is writing &lt;code&gt;.ndjson&lt;/code&gt; files locally:
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Get-ChildItem -Path &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;C:\ProgramData\winlogbeat\opforge-export&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; -Filter *.ndjson
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;-do&#34;&gt;✅ Do&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;1-configure-winlogbeat-to-output-json&#34;&gt;1. Configure Winlogbeat to output JSON&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Edit &lt;code&gt;winlogbeat.yml&lt;/code&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
